This article provides a summary of reactions to President Obama's speech to Muslim communities around the world. According to an online poll conducted by the Broadcasting Board of Governors, more than 75% of respondents viewed the speech favorably. Additionally, over half believed that US policies towards the Arab world and their individual countries would improve based on the speech. The article also highlights various outreach efforts made by US embassies and consulates, including viewing parties, social media engagement, and distribution of the speech to community leaders. The reactions from different countries are also discussed, with positive responses from Afghanistan, India, Lebanon, and the Palestinian Territories. However, there were also calls for concrete actions to follow the speech's rhetoric.